 Competition causes the wasteful duplication of expensive forms of care "Single-Payer FAQ". Physicians for a National Health Program. Retrieved May 30th, 2008 - "When, for example, hospitals compete they often duplicate expensive equipment in order to corner more of the market for lucrative procedure-oriented care. This drives up overall medical costs to pay for the equipment and encourages overtreatment."
